lenders.occupational_info:
My name is Sarah-Elizabeth and I am 17 years old. I love my friends, I love languages and I love to play netball. 
I have three brothers and two sisters. Four of them are adopted. They are S'gaw Karen, a minority group in Burma that have been the victims of a genocide by the Burmese junta for over 60 years. My five siblings are the reason I wake up in the morning, they are everything to me. Without them, I would be nothing.
I have volunteered since I was about 5 years old, beginning by assisting my grandmother give meals to the sick and the elderly through Meals on Wheels. I then volunteered at a St Vincent de Paul Society thrift shop, as well as doing other volunteer work through school. I currently volunteer with the Centacare IHSS program for humanitarian refugees, and have a new-found addiction to Edmund Rice camps. Helping other people has been a passion of mine since I was a little girl and I know that when I am older I'll be working in a humanitarian field. 
My dream is to work on the Thai/Burma border, in the refugee camp that my adopted brothers and sisters came from, helping the Karen people. 
For now, I'll keep making a difference in my own community.
